                        "name": "Focused Assault",
                        "action": {
                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                            "subtype": "action",
                            "name": "Two Actions"
                        },
                        "text": "The hydra attacks a single target with its heads, overwhelming its foe with multiple attacks and leaving almost nowhere to dodge. The hydra Strikes with its fangs. On a successful attack, the hydra deals damage from its fangs Strike to the target, plus an additional 1d6 damage for every head it has beyond the first. Even on a failed attack, the hydra deals the damage from one fangs Strike to the target creature, though it still misses completely on a critical failure. This counts toward the hydra's multiple attack penalty as a number of attacks equal to the number of heads the hydra has."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Storm of Jaws",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "subtype": "offensive_action",
                    "offensive_action_type": "ability",
                    "ability": {
                        "type": "stat_block_section",
                        "subtype": "ability",
